PEPPA’s human friend, Anna, played by South African actress, Ashleigh Butcher has promised fans laughter, cheering and dancing –ahead of the Peppa Pig Live show at the South African State Theatre this weekend. She spoke to the Pretoria News during a photo opportunity with Peppa at the Union Buildings. “We’ve taken the Peppa Pig brand which everyone loves on TV and we’ve translated it into a fully immersive live musical stage show so there’s singalongs and dancealongs and there's lots of interaction for the kids. There’s new music, music from the TV show and there’s a few surprises in store as well,” she said. Butcher said she was excited about the show, adding that she was excited to be back at the theatre. “I’m really excited, I love the State Theatre and I’m really excited to be back there."I’ve done a few shows there.” “Peppa Pig Live in South Africa” is an action-packed stage show, based on the award-winning television series especially designed to give young fans an unforgettable first live theatre experience. Peppa Pig Live has been seen by tens of thousands of children worldwide. Peppa lives with mummy, daddy and little brother, George. The Pretoria News has five family ticket packages to give away to readers. Each winner will receive four tickets, suitable for two adults and two children, for this Saturday’s show at 3.30pm at the State Theatre, Pretoria. To stand a chance to win one of the five sets of tickets for this fun family event, SMS PTANews (SPACE) #PeppaPig followed by your name, surname and e-mail address to 43637. Terms and conditions apply. SMSes costs R1.50. Winners will be notified by Friday.